01:39.224 --> 01:42.727
AND THEY WANT US TO TALK ABOUT
HOW HAPPY WE ARE.

01:42.811 --> 01:45.814
- NO, NO.
WE AGREED NO MORE FUNCTIONS.

01:45.897 --> 01:47.690
THIS IS A FUNCTION.

01:47.774 --> 01:50.693
A FLOATING FUNCTION
FOR WHICH THERE IS NO ESCAPE.

01:50.777 --> 01:53.446
- OKAY, I CAN'T BELIEVE
THAT I'M SAYING THIS,

01:53.530 --> 01:55.031
BUT...

01:55.114 --> 01:59.869
HEY, WHAT IF
I GAVE YOU MY...

01:59.953 --> 02:02.080
DOUCETTE FRERES HANDBAG?

02:02.163 --> 02:05.667
- THE DOUCETTE FRERES?
REALLY?

02:05.750 --> 02:07.669
- WHAT IS IT?

02:07.752 --> 02:10.547
- ONLY THE GREATEST HANDBAG THAT
CIVILIZATION HAS EVER PRODUCED.

02:10.630 --> 02:13.550
- OH, LEATHER AS SOFT
AS A BABY'S BOTTOM

02:13.633 --> 02:17.387
AND TWICE AS USEFUL.

02:17.470 --> 02:19.722
- CRAFTED IN A SMALL TOWN
OF SAINT-AMEDEE

02:19.806 --> 02:22.892
BY A SINGLE FAMILY
WITH TINY HANDS.

02:22.976 --> 02:26.062
THE RESULT OF MERCURY POISONING
IN THE LOCAL RIVER.

02:26.145 --> 02:27.397
- WHEN THEY CLEANED UP
THAT RIVER,

02:27.480 --> 02:31.860
THAT WAS THE END
OF DOUCETTE FRERES.

02:31.943 --> 02:33.736
- OKAY.
I'LL DO IT.

02:33.820 --> 02:34.904
FOR THE BAG.

02:34.988 --> 02:36.406
- ALL RIGHT.
- GREAT.

02:36.489 --> 02:38.741
WELCOME ABOARD.
- WELL, WHO SAID YOU COULD GO?

02:38.825 --> 02:43.955
- WELL, I COULD STAY HOME,
CALL THE PRESS AND OUT YOU.

02:44.038 --> 02:45.915
- ARE YOU WILLING TO BE GAY?

02:45.999 --> 02:47.917
- I'M GAY FOR HEAT.

02:52.839 --> 02:55.925
[upbeat music]

02:56.009 --> 02:57.135
- ♪ BA BA BA BA ♪

