{\an8}- IT'S HUGE.

03:42.931 --> 03:44.432
{\an8}- WELL, NOW.

03:44.515 --> 03:50.313
{\an8}IN SIX DAYS,
IT'LL BE SKINTIGHT.

03:50.396 --> 03:52.982
{\an8}- HELLO, LADIES.
WELCOME ABOARD.

03:53.066 --> 03:55.151
{\an8}I'M CAPTAIN LEBEAU.

03:55.234 --> 03:56.694
{\an8}AND YOU MUST BE
VICTORIA CHASE.

03:56.778 --> 03:58.821
{\an8}- INDEED I AM.
[laughs]

03:58.905 --> 04:03.117
{\an8}- AND YOUR FRIENDS?
- WHO?

04:03.201 --> 04:07.246
{\an8}OH, UH, YES.
THIS IS, UH, MELANIE, ELKA,

04:07.330 --> 04:11.292
{\an8}AND OF COURSE,
MY LOVELY WIFE, JOY.

04:11.376 --> 04:13.294
{\an8}-<i> ENCHANTE.</i>

04:13.378 --> 04:18.675
{\an8}- AREN'T YOU A CHARMING,
CHARMING, CHARMING MAN.

04:18.757 --> 04:21.344
{\an8}- I TRY.
I'LL SEE ALL OF YOU LATER.

04:21.427 --> 04:23.179
{\an8}- YES, YES.
- I CERTAINLY HOPE SO.

04:23.262 --> 04:26.015
{\an8}- I'LL BE IN TOUCH.

04:26.099 --> 04:30.520
{\an8}- WAY TO BE GAY, GUYS.

04:30.603 --> 04:31.729
{\an8}- ALL RIGHT, WELL,
IF WE CAN'T HAVE A MAN,

04:31.813 --> 04:33.231
{\an8}WE CAN AT LEAST
HAVE MANHATTANS.

04:33.314 --> 04:35.316
{\an8}GO FETCH US SOME DRINKS.

04:38.945 --> 04:41.155
- MELANIE?

04:41.239 --> 04:43.116
- [gasps]
CAROLINE.

04:43.199 --> 04:48.246
- OH, MY GOD.
THAT'S MY SISTER.

04:48.329 --> 04:50.415
I CAN'T BELIEVE THIS.

04:50.498 --> 04:52.208
- I DIDN'T EVEN KNOW
YOU WERE GAY.

04:52.291 --> 04:56.129
- THIS IS BLOWING MY MIND.
WE'RE BOTH GAY.

04:57.964 --> 04:59.382
- [stammering]
YEAH. RIGHT.

04:59.465 --> 05:01.676
BECAUSE WHY ELSE WOULD
WE BE ON A GAY CRUISE?

05:01.759 --> 05:07.432
- CAROLINE, BABY.
MOMMY'S THIRSTY.

05:07.515 --> 05:09.058
- MELANIE, THIS IS
MY GIRLFRIEND, NAN.

05:09.142 --> 05:11.060
NAN, THIS IS MY SISTER, MELANIE.
SHE'S GAY.

05:11.144 --> 05:13.604
- [laughs]
